<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1440,1424,1720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName authority="Levichev (1990)" authorityName="Levichev" authorityYear="1990" box="[151,600,1424,1450]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Foliatae">
<emphasis box="[151,229,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Gagea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[298,397,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Foliatae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Levichev, I. G." box="[405,600,1424,1450]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="225 - 234" refId="ref9564" refString="Levichev, I. G. (1990) The synopsis of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) from the western Tien-Shan. (in Russian). Botanicheskii Zhurnal 75: 225 - 234." type="journal article" year="1990">Levichev (1990)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was not accepted as a distinct section by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[1094,1353,1424,1450]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1204,1263,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was initially published including 
<taxonomicName authority="(J. Presl &amp; C. Presl) Schultes &amp; Schultes (1830: 1073)" authorityName="Schultes &amp; Schultes (1830:" authorityPageNumber="1073" authorityYear="1073" baseAuthorityName="J. Presl &amp; C. Presl" box="[489,1235,1462,1488]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis box="[489,601,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. foliosa</emphasis>
(J.Presl &amp; C.Presl) 
<bibRefCitation author="Schultes, A. &amp; Schultes, H." box="[836,1235,1462,1488]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="1703 - 1703" refId="ref10793" refString="Schultes, A. &amp; Schultes, H. (1830) Gagea. Systema Vegetabilium 7: 1703 - 1703." type="journal article" year="1830">Schultes &amp; Schultes (1830: 1073)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascher" authorityYear="1904" box="[1247,1354,1463,1488]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenera">
<emphasis box="[1247,1354,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. tenera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lang) Bess. ex Schultes &amp; Schultes (1829: 550)" authorityName="Schultes &amp; Schultes" authorityPageNumber="550" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="Lang" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="szovitsii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G. szovitsii</emphasis>
(Lang) Bess. ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Schultes, A. &amp; Schultes, H." box="[449,839,1501,1527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="536 - 554" refId="ref10771" refString="Schultes, A. &amp; Schultes, H. (1829) Gagea. Systema Vegetabilium 7: 536 - 554." type="journal article" year="1829">Schultes &amp; Schultes (1829: 550)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. All these species were later transferred to 
<emphasis box="[1350,1375,1501,1526]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[151,330,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[378,652,1540,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[494,556,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
. Species of this section and 
<emphasis box="[1007,1033,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[1107,1235,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Fistulosae</emphasis>
are collectively monophyletic based on analyses of molecular data conducted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[914,1169,1578,1604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1023,1081,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Peruzzi, L. &amp; Peterson, A. &amp; Tison, J. - M. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[1182,1436,1578,1604]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="219 - 234" refId="ref10138" refString="Peruzzi, L., Peterson, A., Tison, J. - M. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008 a) Phylogenetic relationships of Gagea Salisb. (Liliaceae) in Italy, inferred from molecular and morphological data matrices. Plant Systematics and Evolution 276: 219 - 234." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peruzzi 
<emphasis box="[1277,1335,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2008 
<emphasis box="[1412,1426,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">a</emphasis>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[201,428,1617,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[279,338,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Levichev" authorityName="Levichev" box="[438,944,1617,1643]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="6" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Didymobulbos">
<emphasis box="[438,516,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Gagea</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[584,828,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos sensu</emphasis>
Levichev
</taxonomicName>
is not monophyletic. Anatomical features of the pedicel and the basal leaf are characteristic of all members of both 
<emphasis box="[1109,1136,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sections 
<emphasis box="[1259,1381,1656,1681]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Stipitatae</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[151,322,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
. It is clear that Pascher's treatment of 
<emphasis box="[769,794,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[861,1032,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="50">Didymobulbos</emphasis>
should be accepted.
</paragraph>
